definition.value: The trisodium salt of citric acid.
A macromolecule composed of repeating propyleneoxy units.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound composed of repeating beta-(1->4)-linked 6-azido-6-deoxyglucose units.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound formed by nitrating cellulose through exposure to nitric acid or another powerful nitrating agent.
Any fatty acid containing at least one C=C double bond.
A poly(ethylene glycol) compound having a methacrylate group at the alpha-terminus and a methyl group at the omega-terminus.
A poly(ethylene glycol) compound terminated with methacrylate groups.
A poly(ethylene glycol) compound terminated with acrylate groups.
A polymer composed of repeating hydroxyalkanoyl units.
A polymer composed of repeating hydroxybutyryl units.
A polymer composed of repeating 3-hydroxybutyryl units.
A polymer composed of repeating hydroxypentanoyl units.
A polymer composed of repeating 3-hydroxypentanoyl units.
A polymer composed of repeating 5-hydroxypentanoyl units.

A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan [2-(1,2-dihydroxyethyl)tetrahydrofuran-3,4-diol] normally containing a total of 20 oxyethylene groups, with one or more of the terminal hydroxy groups esterified with a fatty acyl group. They are used as emulsifiers and dispersing agents in some pharmaceuticals products and as defoamers and emulsifiers in some foods.

Any poly(ethylene glycol) derivative composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan [2-(1,2-dihydroxyethyl)tetrahydrofuran-3,4-diol] normally containing a total of 20 oxyethylene groups, with one or more of the terminal hydroxy groups esterified with a fatty acyl group. They are used as emulsifiers and dispersing agents in some pharmaceuticals products and as defoamers and emulsifiers in some foods.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a palmitoyl group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a dodecanoyl group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a stearate group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by an oleoyl group.
A hydrate that is the hexahydrate of nickel sulfate.
A compound of iron and sulfate in which the ratio of iron(3+) to sulfate ions is 3:2.
The hexahydrate of chromium(3+) trichloride.
A potassium salt that is the dipotassium salt of dichromic acid.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound formed by methylating cellulose through exposure to NaOH/CH3Cl.
A poly(ethylene glycol) derivative that is poly(ethylene glycol) in which one of the terminal hydroxy groups has been converted to the corresponding methyl ether.
A poly(ethylene glycol) terminated with a methyl group at one end.
D-Xylose in its pyranose form.
A compound of cobalt and sulfate in which the ratio of cobalt (+2 oxidation state) to sulfate is 1:1.
A compound of chromium and sulfate in which the ratio of chromium (in the +3 oxidation state) to sulfate is 2:3
An inorganic chloride of copper in which the metal is in the +1 oxidation state.
A metal sulfate in which the metal is beryllium (in the +2 oxidation state) and the ratio of beryllium  to sulfate is 1:1.
A metal sulfate in which the counterion is lithium and the ratio of lithium to sulfate is 2:1.
The all-cis-isomer of a C22 polyunsaturated fatty acid having five double bonds in the 7-, 10-, 13-, 16- and 19-positions.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound formed by total acetylation of cellulose.
A hydrate of beryllium sulfate containing beryllium (in +2 oxidation state), sulfate and  water moieties in the ratio 1:1:4.
A hydrate of cobalt chloride containing cobalt (in +2 oxidation state), chloride and water moieties in the ratio 1:2:6.
A hydrate of nickel sulfate containing nickel (in +2 oxidation state), sulfate and water moieties in the ratio 1:1:7.
A poly(ethylene glycol) terminated with -NH2 groups.
A hydrate of nickel chloride containing nickel (in the +2 oxidation state), chloride and water moeities in the ratio 1:2:6.
A hexitol compound with the 2-hydroxy substituent either absent or replaced by a different functional group.
The (R)-enantiomer of gatifloxacin.
The (S)-enantiomer of gatifloxacin.
An inorganic salt of sodium, the anion of which is the aurothiosulfate(3-) linear coordination complex.
The hydrochloride salt of L-lysine

A monohydroxybenzoic acid consisting of 2-hydroxybenzoic acid having nitro substituents at the 3- and 5-positions. It is used in colorimetric testing for the presence of free carbonyl groups (C=O) in reducing sugars.
A cephalosporin compound having (R)-O-formylmandelamido and N-methylthiotetrazole side groups. It is used (as the sodium salt) as a progrug for cefamandole.
Any organic heterotricyclic compound based on a skeleton comprised of an oxazine ring fused onto a quinoline system.
The hydrate that is the monohydrate of the cephalosporin cefadroxil.
A derivative of p-salicylic acid with chloro- substituents at C-3 and C-5 of the benzene ring.
The conjugate base of 3,5-dichlorohydroxybenzoic acid. Comprising a 3,5-dihydroxybenzoic acid core with the carboxylic acid proton missing, giving a charge of -1.
